summary.dataset_description: This dataset contains information about the population, number of engineers, and number of hurricanes in each state of the United States.

goals.question: What is the correlation between the percentage of engineers and the population in each state?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of engineers vs population
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand if there is a relationship between the percentage of engineers and the population in each state. It can also help us identify any outliers or patterns in the data.

goals.question: Which state has the highest percentage of engineers?
goals.visualization: bar chart of engineers by state
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us identify the state with the highest percentage of engineers and compare it to other states. It can also help us understand the distribution of engineers across different states.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='population', y='engineers', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the percentage of engineers and the population in each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage of Engineers')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='state', y='engineers', data=data, order=data.sort_values('engineers', ascending=False)['state'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which state has the highest percentage of engineers?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='hurricanes', hue='state', multiple='stack')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of hurricanes across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
